result.adr_address: 37 Leighton Rd, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 37 Leighton Rd, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Mak's Noodle

reviews.text: I go to Mak’s noodles every single time on my business trip to HK. It’s a perfect dinner or supper with its delectable wanton noodles or beef brisket noodles (both of my favourites) and an add-on of its vegetables with oyster sauce if I’m feeling greedy. Noodles are extremely “bouncy” and the broth is not too salty and doesn’t taste like it’s MSG overload. Don’t expect huge portion noodles but this is exactly why I love it, it doesn’t leave you feeling too full but just satisfactory enough.
Beef brisket noodle was awesome! Wanton noodle was good as well. This is a good spot for those looking for a quick bite of some local Hong Kong cuisine. Definitely worth trying!
fantastic noodles for a good price. definitely a place to go if you’re in the area and hungry

A place to go to enjoy classic wonton noodle soup Hong Kong style. Thin noodle, delicate wonton, tasty soup. Local would add vinegar and pepper to further spice up the soup base.  Green themed interior, CLEAN which is a rare indulgence when it comes to classic noodle, fast food cafe in HK.  Small portion so may have to order beyond one dish per person.
Small bowls, very yummy.  Definitely a place to get HK style noodles , wontons and dumplings.
